author: Inside Edition
description: A woman collapsed in joy after winning a piece of history at an auction. Her winning bid of $520,000 nabbed a dress once owned by Princess Diana. Renae Plant shared a special connection to the dress. An image shows Plant's hand about to shake Princess Diana's hand back in 1988 when Diana wore the dress for the first time during a visit to Australia, where Plant grew up. The dress is known as the "caring dress." Inside Edition was with Plant when she went to Julien's Auction House in Los Angeles to pick it up.
title: Joyous Woman Collapses After Winning Princess Diana's Dress

author: Inside Edition
description: Hurricane Erin is hundreds of miles wide and growing. One ocean-rescue official says Erin is triggering dangerous rip tides "several blocks wide." In Seabright, New Jersey, winds are  picking up and red flags are posted telling swimmers to stay out of the water. All beaches along the Jersey Shore are closed. Double red flags were also flying at beaches in Maryland and Massachusetts. It's feared waves along the east coast could hit 20 feet.
title: Hurricane Erin Triggers Dangerous Rip Currents

author: Inside Edition
description: The parents of Cile Steward, one of the kids still missing from Camp Mystic are speaking out. Eight-year-old Cile was swept away in the horrific Texas floods. Cile's father wiped tears as his wife testified Wednesday in support of new state legislation that would bolster safety at summer camps. The parents of 9-year-old Lila Bonner also provided testimony. Lila's mother, Kaitlyn, had spent 10 summers at Camp Mystic.
title: Parents of Missing Kids From Camp Mystic Testify

author: Inside Edition
description: "The Biggest Loser" was a controversial television series. Millions watched as obese contestants competed to shed massive amounts of weight. Now, a new Netflix documentary "Fit for TV: The Reality of The Biggest Loser," is shedding light on the dark side of the show. Tracy Yukich nearly died during a grueling, mile-long run in 90-degree heat and was rushed to a hospital. She spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall.
title: New Netflix Documentary Reveals Dark Side of 'The Biggest Loser'

author: Inside Edition
description: A little girl accidentally knocked over a marble table at a coffee shop, and her mother says she was stunned by what happened next.
title: Little Girl Breaks Expensive Table in Coffee Shop #shorts

description: Rebecca claimed she was changing 7-month-old Emmanuel Haro's diapers in a parking lot outside a sporting goods store when he was kidnapped.
title: Cops Find 'Inconsistencies' After Mom Claims Baby Was Kidnapped #shorts
